---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — DeviceLab"
  description="How DeviceLab scores devices, how the mixer works, and what stays deterministic."
>
  <section class="dl-page-header">
    <div class="dl-eyebrow-hero">DEVICELAB / ABOUT</div>
    <h1>How the lab works</h1>
    <p class="dl-blurb">
      DeviceLab is a small, opinionated device ranker. We score every device
      on six axes and let you weight them yourself. This page is the
      contract for how that works.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="dl-container" style="padding: 12px 16px 40px; max-width: 68ch;">
    <h2>Scoring</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Six axes: performance, portability, display, battery, build, value.</li>
      <li>Each axis is 0–100.</li>
      <li>The composite is a normalised weighted mean.</li>
      <li>Ties break on <span class="mono">value</span>, then alphabetically.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Nothing about the ranking depends on price feeds, affiliate
        offers, or sponsorship.</strong> If a merchant tries to pay for a
        higher rank, the answer is no. Ingestion sits in a separate module
        with a hard boundary to the scoring engine.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Presets</h2>
    <p>
      Presets are named weight vectors mapped to a URL like <span class="mono">/best-laptops-for-students</span>.
      Each one prewires the mixer to what a specific persona typically cares
      about — you can still slide any axis to override it.
    </p>

    <h2>Price tracking</h2>
    <p>
      "Track price" opens an email capture that stores (email, device, target
      price) in Cloudflare KV. When the price pipeline lands, a scheduled job
      will diff incoming price points against saved targets and send at most
      one email per trigger. No newsletter.
    </p>

    <h2>Roadmap markers in the code</h2>
    <p>
      Two integration points are stubbed and marked in the codebase:
    </p>
    <ul class="mono" style="font-size: 13px;">
      <li>TODO(ingestion) — where the n8n price job writes offers + priceHistory.</li>
      <li>TODO(affiliate) — where merchant deep links get tracking params appended.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Base>
